place.name: STAWELL
place.gazetteerText: STAWELL, a chapelry in Moorlinch parish, Somerset; 4 miles E by N of Bridgewater r. station. Post town Bridgewater. Acres, 973. Real property, £2,207. Pop., 173. Houses, 47. The living is annexed to Moorlinch. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
